title: 500+ applications, 0 interviews - what am I doing wrong?
selftext: I graduated 6 months ago with a CS degree from a state school. I've applied to over 500 positions and haven't gotten a single interview. My GPA is 3.5, I have 2 internships, and several personal projects. I'm starting to lose hope. Any advice?
author: desperate_grad

title: What tools do you use to tailor your resume for each application?
selftext: I know you're supposed to customize your resume for each job, but that takes forever. Are there any tools or techniques you use to speed up this process while still making each application count?
author: efficient_job_hunter
